1 AN ACT concerning crimes, punishment and criminal procedure; relating
2 to the crimes of trespassing on a critical infrastructure facility and
3 criminal damage to a critical infrastructure facility; defining a critical
4 infrastructure facility used for telecommunications or video services to
5 include aboveground and belowground lines, cables and, wires and
6 certain other structures and equipment; amending K.S.A. 21-5818
7 and repealing the existing section.
8
9 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
10 Section 1. K.S.A. 21-5818 is hereby amended to read as follows: 21-
11 5818. (a) Trespassing on a critical infrastructure facility is, without consent
12 of the owner or the owner's agent, knowingly entering or remaining in:
13 (1) A critical infrastructure facility; or
14 (2) any property containing a critical infrastructure facility, if such
15 property is completely enclosed by a fence or other physical barrier that is
16 obviously designed to exclude intruders or is clearly marked with a sign or
17 signs that are posted on the property that are reasonably likely to come to
18 the attention of intruders and indicate that entry is forbidden without site
19 authorization.
20 (b) Aggravated trespassing on a critical infrastructure facility is:
21 (1) Knowingly entering or remaining in:
22 (A) A critical infrastructure facility; or
23 (B) any property containing a critical infrastructure facility, if such
24 property is completely enclosed by a fence or other physical barrier that is
25 obviously designed to exclude intruders or is clearly marked with a sign or
26 signs that are posted on the property that are reasonably likely to come to
27 the attention of intruders and indicate that entry is forbidden without site
28 authorization; and
29 (2) with the intent to damage, destroy or tamper with a critical
30 infrastructure facility or impede or inhibit operations of the facility.
31 (c) Criminal damage to a critical infrastructure facility is knowingly
32 damaging, destroying or tampering with a critical infrastructure facility.
33 (d) Aggravated criminal damage to a critical infrastructure facility is
34 knowingly damaging, destroying or tampering with a critical infrastructure
35 facility with the intent to impede or inhibit operations of the facility.

HB 2061—Am. by HC 2
1 (e) (1) Trespassing on a critical infrastructure facility is a class A
2 nonperson misdemeanor.
3 (2) Aggravated trespassing on a critical infrastructure facility is a
4 severity level 7, nonperson felony.
5 (3) Criminal damage to a critical infrastructure facility is a severity
6 level 6, nonperson felony.
7 (4) Aggravated criminal damage to a critical infrastructure facility is
8 a severity level 5, nonperson felony.
9 (f) Nothing in this section shall be construed to prevent:
10 (1) An owner or operator of a critical infrastructure facility that has
11 been damaged from pursuing any other remedy in law or equity; or
12 (2) a person who violates the provisions of this section from being
13 prosecuted for, convicted of and punished for any other offense in article
14 58 of chapter 21 of the Kansas Statutes Annotated, and amendments
15 thereto, or K.S.A. 66-2303, and amendments thereto.
16 (g) As used in this section, "critical infrastructure facility" means any:
17 (1) Petroleum or alumina refinery;
18 (2) electric generation facility, substation, switching station, electrical
19 control center, electric distribution or transmission lines, or associated
20 equipment infrastructure;
21 (3) chemical, polymer or rubber manufacturing facility;
22 (4) water supply diversion, production, treatment, storage or
23 distribution facility and appurtenances, including, but not limited to,
24 underground pipelines and a wastewater treatment plant or pump station;
25 (5) natural gas compressor station;
26 (6) liquid natural gas or propane terminal or storage facility;
27 (7) facility that is used for wireline, broadband or wireless
28 telecommunications or video services infrastructure whether such facility
29 is located within or outside of any public or highway right-of-way,
30 including, but not limited to:
31 (A) Aboveground and belowground lines, cable or wires;
32 (B) backup power supplies; and
33 (C) cable television headend;
34 (D) antennas, radio transceivers, towers, wireless support
35 structures, small cell facilities and any associated support structures
36 and accessory equipment; and
37 (E) equipment buildings, cabinets and storage sheds, shelters or
38 similar structures;
39 (8) port, railroad switching yard, railroad tracks, trucking terminal or
40 other freight transportation facility;
41 (9) gas processing plant, including a plant used in the processing,
42 treatment or fractionation of natural gas, propane or natural gas liquids;
43 (10) transmission facility used by a federally licensed radio or

